\n```\nPOST /oauth/token\nContent-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded\n\ngrant_type=client_credentials&client_id=YOUR_ID&client_secret=YOUR_SECRET\n```\n\nThe response contains an `access_token` that is valid for 3600 seconds. Include it in subsequent requests:\n\n```\nAuthorization: Bearer <access_token>\n```\n\n## Token Expiration & Refresh\n\nWhen an access token expires the API returns a `401 Unauthorized` error (see [Errors](errors.md)). Re-authenticate by requesting a new token using the same client-credentials flow described above.\n\n## Best Practices\n\n- Store credentials securely; never commit them to version control.\n- Rotate API keys regularly.\n- Use the shortest token lifetime that fits your workflow.\n"}, {"path": "mkdocs.yml", "content": "site_name: Clean MkDocs Benchmark\nsite_description: Documentation benchmark repository\nnav:\n  - Home: index.md\n  - Getting Started: getting-started.md\n  - Configuration: configuration.md\n  - API:\n      - Overview: api/overview.md\n      - Authentication: api/authentication.md\n      - Errors: api/errors.md\ntheme:\n  name: material\nmarkdown_extensions:\n  - admonition\n"}], "message": "docs(api): add authentication reference page and wire it into mkdocs navigation\n\nImplements the maintenance request from Issue #1:\n- Expand docs/api/authentication.md with API key and OAuth 2.0 authentication documentation\n- Add Authentication entry to the API section of mkdocs.yml navigation", "owner": "rpnr-bench", "repo": "T16_R02_C01_A02"}, "id": "call_fc8fc6b96930410e91c764db", "type": "tool_call"}], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 11077, "output_tokens": 645, "total_tokens": 11722, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 10176}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 33}}}}]}}}
