{"ts": "2026-06-09T05:54:26.672268+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "Both the individual and batch commit approaches returned a **403 – Resource not accessible by personal access token**, which means the GitHub token provided lacks write (push) access to this repository. Retrying won't fix a permissions issue.\n\n---\n\n## Summary of the work completed\n\n### Issue #1 – \"Add authentication API docs\"\n\nThe issue requests two changes:\n\n1. **Create / expand `docs/api/authentication.md`** with real authentication reference content.\n2. **Wire it into the MkDocs navigation** in `mkdocs.yml`.\n\n### Current state\n\n- **`docs/api/authentication.md`** already exists but contains only a stub:\n  ```\n  # Authentication\n  Authentication reference material will be documented here.\n  ```\n- **`mkdocs.yml`** does **not** include the authentication page in the `nav` section — the `API` sub-nav has only `Overview` and `Errors`.\n\n### Planned changes (ready to commit when write access is available)\n\n**`docs/api/authentication.md`** – replace the stub with a full reference covering:\n- Overview of supported methods (API Key & OAuth 2.0 Client Credentials)\n- API Key authentication (Bearer header usage, scoping, rotation)\n- OAuth 2.0 Client Credentials flow (token request/response, header usage)\n- Token expiration & refresh behaviour (link to the Errors page)\n- Best-practice guidance (secure storage, rotation, lifetime)\n\n**`mkdocs.yml`** – add the `Authentication` entry to the `API` sub-navigation:\n\n```yaml\n  - API:\n      - Overview: api/overview.md\n      - Authentication: api/authentication.md   # ← new\n      - Errors: api/errors.md\n```\n\n### What's blocking\n\nThe repository token does not have **write/push** permission, so neither the single-file nor the multi-file commit could be applied. Once a token with `contents: write` scope is available, the two changes above can be committed in one push.", "additional_kwar